# Case Study Development Rules

## Required Skills

Before working on case studies, read:
- `plugins/portfolio-tools/skills/case-study-builder/SKILL.md`
- `plugins/portfolio-tools/skills/image-manager/SKILL.md`

## Data Structure

Case studies are defined in `data/case-studies.ts`:

```tsx
export interface CaseStudy {
  id: number
  title: string
  description: string
  image: string           // Thumbnail path
  href: string            // URL path
  color: string           // CSS variable like 'var(--color-0)'
  subtitle?: string       // Optional subtitle
}
```

## Adding a New Case Study

### 1. Add to data file (`data/case-studies.ts`)

```tsx
{
  id: 2,  // Next available ID
  title: 'Project Name',
  description: 'Brief description for cards and previews.',
  image: '/images/case-studies/project-name/thumb/thumb.webp',
  href: '/case-studies/project-name',
  color: 'var(--color-2)',
  subtitle: 'Category & Role',
}
```

### 2. Create page (`app/case-studies/project-name/page.tsx`)

```tsx
import { Metadata } from 'next'
import CaseStudyHero from '@/components/case-studies/CaseStudyHero'
import CaseStudySection from '@/components/case-studies/CaseStudySection'
import CaseStudyImage from '@/components/case-studies/CaseStudyImage'
import CaseStudyNext from '@/components/case-studies/CaseStudyNext'

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Project Name | Raúl Mermans',
  description: 'Case study description for SEO.',
}

export default function ProjectNamePage() {
  return (
    <main className="case-study">
      <CaseStudyHero
        title="Project Name"
        subtitle="Category"
        description="Hero description text."
        color="var(--color-2)"
      />
      
      <CaseStudySection title="Section Title">
        <p>Section content...</p>
      </CaseStudySection>
      
      <CaseStudyImage
        src="/images/case-studies/project-name/image.webp"
        alt="Descriptive alt text"
      />
      
      <CaseStudyNext currentHref="/case-studies/project-name" />
    </main>
  )
}
```

### 3. Add images

```
public/images/case-studies/project-name/
  ├── thumb/
  │   └── thumb.webp     # Thumbnail (800x600 recommended)
  ├── hero.webp          # Hero image
  └── *.webp             # Additional images
```

## Available Components

```tsx
// Hero section with title and description
<CaseStudyHero title="" subtitle="" description="" color="" />

// Content section with optional title
<CaseStudySection title="">
  <p>Content...</p>
</CaseStudySection>

// Full-width image
<CaseStudyImage src="" alt="" />

// Image gallery
<CaseStudyGallery images={[{ src: '', alt: '' }]} />

// Next case study CTA
<CaseStudyNext currentHref="/case-studies/current" />

// Metadata display
<CaseStudyMeta items={[{ label: 'Role', value: 'Designer' }]} />
```

## Image Guidelines

- Use `.webp` format for all images
- Thumbnails: 800x600px recommended
- Hero images: 1920px width max
- Always include descriptive `alt` text
- Use `priority` prop for above-fold images
